('5905ffd8-2602-5e59-9246-0f9efffee2ae', '155a8a93-ae29-4a37-b21f-da115600eaad', 'Watching funny animal clips on YouTube provides much ___ for many people after a long day of work.', '在 YouTube 上觀看有趣的動物影片，可以為許多人在漫長的工作日後提供許多消遣。', 'amusement', 'frustration', 'confidence', 'confusion', 'amuse (使歡笑) + -ment (名詞字尾) → amusement (樂趣、消遣)', 'amuse 聽起來像 a muse (靈感女神)，想像靈感女神帶給你快樂與樂趣。', '2026-07-06 20:58:28', '2026-07-06 20:58:28'),
('c8e87d0b-f5cb-5c46-878c-44b1ccfe528a', '746ae30c-4abc-447b-ae51-8cc35436e601', 'Experts ___ the sudden increase in crime rates to the growing unemployment rate.', '專家將犯罪率的突然上升歸因於失業率的增加。', 'attribute', 'distribute', 'contribute', 'determine', 'tribute 意為『給予』；at- (指向) + tribute (給予) → 將特質指向某物 → 歸因於。', '利用句型 attribute A to B (將 A 歸因於 B) 來記憶。', '2026-07-07 02:30:02', '2026-07-07 02:30:02'),
('4fca07fc-5d42-5ded-b83a-08b041d8af32', '1d25b915-249a-4abe-84ed-99f9f2531942', 'The sudden, loud noise in the middle of the night was enough to ___ the sleeping neighbors.', '半夜突然發出的巨大噪音足以喚醒熟睡的鄰居。', 'awaken', 'comfort', 'reward', 'nourish', 'a- (使動/向) + wake (醒) + -en (使動字尾) → 喚醒', 'wake 是「醒來」，加上 -en 字尾變成「使...醒來」的動詞。', '2026-07-07 04:14:50', '2026-07-07 04:14:50'),
('edd0a8ba-eb15-569b-8651-5ce6f60bc252', 'bb3d5d7b-762d-4dd6-93e2-cb573a7a603e', 'The sudden noise caused the deer to run ___ into the forest.', '突然的噪音導致鹿群跑進森林裡。', 'away', 'near', 'back', 'down', 'a- (向/處於某種狀態) + way (道路/方向) → 往某個方向前進 → 離開。', '想像走在 a way (一條路) 上，越走越遠就變成 away (離開)。', '2026-07-07 04:18:43', '2026-07-07 04:18:43'),
